enhanced_by.reason: Both methods validate IP addresses, with isValidInet6Address potentially reusing parts of isValidInet4Address for embedded IPv4 addresses.
The method match(String) from RegexValidator is used in isValidInet4Address and can be reused for similar regex matching in isValidInet6Address.
Both methods return a boolean indicating the validity of an address, which can inform the construction of assertions for isValidInet6Address.
The method validate(String) from RegexValidator performs validation similar to isValidInet6Address, which can inform the construction of assertions.
